.NET Framework 3.5.name: OptitrackSkeletonAnimator
.NET Framework 3.5.summary: Implements live retargeting of streamed OptiTrack skeletal data via Mecanim. Add this component to an imported model GameObject that has a properly configured humanoid Avatar definition.
.NET Framework 3.5.remarks: A hierarchy of GameObjects (see m_rootObject and m_boneObjectMap ) will be created to receive the streaming pose data for the skeleton asset specified by SkeletonAssetName. A source Avatar will be created automatically from the streamed skeleton definition.

fields.name: DestinationAvatar
fields.summary: The humanoid avatar for this GameObject's imported model.

fields.name: m_boneObjectMap
fields.summary: Maps between OptiTrack skeleton bone IDs and corresponding GameObjects.

fields.name: m_cachedMecanimBoneNameMap
fields.summary: Maps between Mecanim anatomy bone names (keys) and streamed bone names from various naming conventions supported by the OptiTrack software (values). Populated by String).

fields.name: m_destPoseHandler
fields.summary: Set up to write poses to this GameObject using DestinationAvatar.

fields.name: m_humanPose
fields.summary: Used when retrieving and retargeting source pose. Cached and reused for efficiency.

fields.name: m_rootObject
fields.summary: The root GameObject of the streamed skeletal pose transform hierarchy.

fields.name: m_srcPoseHandler
fields.summary: Set up to read poses from our streamed GameObject transform hierarchy.

fields.name: SkeletonAssetName
fields.summary: The name of the skeleton asset in the stream that will provide retargeting source data.

fields.name: StreamingClient
fields.summary: The client object to use for receiving streamed skeletal pose data.

methods.name: CacheBoneNameMap(OptitrackBoneNameConvention convention, string assetName)
methods.summary: Updates the m_cachedMecanimBoneNameMap lookup to reflect the specified bone naming convention and source skeleton asset name.

params.value: The bone naming convention to use. Must match the host software.
The name of the source skeleton asset.

methods.name: MecanimSetup(string rootObjectName)
methods.summary: Constructs the source Avatar and pose handlers for Mecanim retargeting.

methods.name: Start()
